The [[FHS]] or [[Filesystem Hierarchy Standard]] is:

<blockquote>A set of requirements and guidelines for file and directory placement under UNIX-like operating systems. The guidelines are intended to support interoperability of applications, system administration tools, development tools, and scripts as well as greater uniformity of documentation for these systems.</blockquote>

